Fast-rising Nigerian singer, Ade Ebenezer Olufemi, popularly known as Olakira says no need to brag about achievement or finances. Olakira, in a post on Saturday, said numbers don’t lie, hence no need for needless bragging. According to him, needless bragging makes you an empty barrel. He tweeted, “Needless bragging makes you an empty barrel, numbers don’t lie.” This is coming after Burna Boy bragged that he’s the highest-paid artiste in Africa. According to him, he knows what everyone earns and he’s richer than Wizkid and Davido put together. 